\chapter{Library Profiles}
\label{ch:profiles}

This chapter documents the specific holdings of every library system in which at least one surveyed title was found. The {{ stats.systemCount }} systems are grouped into three tiers by collection depth: Tier~1 (20 or more titles) receives a complete book-by-book inventory; Tier~2 (5--19 titles) receives a summary listing; Tier~3 (1--4 titles) is listed in compact form. A parent in Plano should be able to find, in these pages, exactly which harmful titles sit on the shelves of the Plano Public Library, and a trustee in Wichita Falls should be able to see how that system's acquisitions compare with peer institutions.

