\section{Tier 3 --- Minimal Holdings (1--4 titles)}

The remaining {{ tier3 | length }} systems hold between 1 and 4 surveyed titles. In most cases these are small-town and rural libraries that acquired one or two widely promoted books---often award winners pushed into their collections through bulk purchasing programs. Even a single harmful title on the shelf matters, because in a small town the public library may be the only place a child encounters this material.

